[195.50068, "o", "\u001b[1;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[2m[\u001b[0m\u001b[92m✓\u001b[0m\u001b[2m] \u001b[0m\u001b[1;97mIteration 2 / 100\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(52318 tok)\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(2m 12s)\u001b[0m\u001b[2;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[2m  Think: \u001b[0m\u001b[2mTurn 1, no real history. The user wants a feature-planning workflow for adding a --verbose flag. I \u001b[0m\u001b[3;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mneed to: bootstrap the dossier first, surface acceptance criteria, then run explore + plan stages, \u001b[0m\u001b[4;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mthen FINALIZE as :partial (two-step). No exec, recommend-only. Step 1: Resolve template. Let me list \u001b[0m\u001b[5;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mtemplates and find a feature-planning / feature-launch fit. Compute deterministic id, probe resume, \u001b[0m\u001b[6;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mthen bootstrap. I'll do this in one clojure fence to gather template + id + resume state first, then \u001b[0m\u001b[7;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mbootstrap based on what's available. Let me start by discovering templates and computing the id.\u001b[0m\u001b[8;1H\u001b[2K  \u001b[2m• Code:\u001b[0m\u001b[9;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m┌─\u001b[0m\u001b[10;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m(def templates (:templates (workflow$list-templates)))\u001b[0m\u001b[1"]
[195.500697, "o", "1;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m(println \"TEMPLATES:\")\u001b[0m\u001b[12;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m(doseq [t templates] (println \"-\" (:id t) \"|\" (:source t) \"|\" (:description t)))\u001b[0m\u001b[13;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m(def wid (:slug (workflow$id :template :feature-launch\u001b[0m\u001b[14;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m                             :question \"Run a feature-planning workflow for adding a --verbose flag to\u001b[0m\u001b[15;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35mthis CLI\")))\u001b[0m\u001b[16;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m(println \"WID:\" wid)\u001b[0m\u001b[17;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m(println \"RESUME:\" (workflow$resume? :id wid))\u001b[0m\u001b[18;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m└─\u001b[0m\u001b[19;1H\u001b[2K  \u001b[2m• Output:\u001b[0m\u001b[20;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m┌─\u001b[0m\u001b[21;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0mTEMPLATES:\u001b[22;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0mWID: feature-launch--feature-planning-workflow-adding-verbose-flag-cli\u001b[23;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0mRESUME: {:exists? false}\u001b[24;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m└─\u001b[0m\u001b[25;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[2m[\u001b[0m\u001b[1;96m+\u001b[0m\u001b[2m] \u001b[0m\u001b[1;97mIteration 3 / 100\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(124840 tok)\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(47.1s)\u001b[0m\u001b[26;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[2m  Think: \u001b["]
[195.500717, "o", "0m\u001b[2mIteration 2 showed templates list printed empty (no built-in feature-launch found via list-templates \u001b[0m\u001b[27;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mdoseq), but WID computed and resume says not-exists. I should try loading the feature-launch template \u001b[0m\u001b[28;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mdirectly (load-template resolves built-ins via classpath even if list didn't show them). If it loads, \u001b[0m\u001b[29;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mbootstrap with its acceptance + stages but tailor stages to the user's request: explore + plan only \u001b[0m\u001b[30;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2m(no exec — recommend-only). If load fails, fall back to :ad-hoc with hand-drafted stages. Let me load \u001b[0m\u001b[31;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mthe template and inspect it first, then bootstrap. I'll do the load + inspect in one fence so I can \u001b[0m\u001b[32;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2msee acceptance/stages structure before bootstrapping.\u001b[0m\u001b[33;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[2m[\u001b[0m\u001b[1;93m⠸\u001b[0m\u001b[2m]\u001b[0m \u001b[96mReasoning...\u001b[0m\u001b[2m (3m 7s)\u001b[0m"]
