[195.508191, "o", "\u001b[1;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mdoseq), but WID computed and resume says not-exists. I should try loading the feature-launch template \u001b[0m\u001b[2;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mdirectly (load-template resolves built-ins via classpath even if list didn't show them). If it loads, \u001b[0m\u001b[3;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mbootstrap with its acceptance + stages but tailor stages to the user's request: explore + plan only \u001b[0m\u001b[4;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2m(no exec — recommend-only). If load fails, fall back to :ad-hoc with hand-drafted stages. Let me load \u001b[0m\u001b[5;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mthe template and inspect it first, then bootstrap. I'll do the load + inspect in one fence so I can \u001b[0m\u001b[6;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2msee acceptance/stages structure before bootstrapping.\u001b[0m\u001b[7;1H\u001b[2K  \u001b[2m• Code:\u001b[0m\u001b[8;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m┌─\u001b[0m\u001b[9;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m(def tmpl-load (workflow$load-template :id :feature-launch))\u001b[0m\u001b[10;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m(println \"LOAD-SOURCE:\" (:source tmpl-load))\u001b[0m\u001b[11;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m(println \"LOAD-ERROR:\" (:error tmpl-l"]
