[301.101915, "o", "\r\n\u001b[2m┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m│\u001b[0m \u001b[1m\u001b[96mBrainyard TUI\u001b[0m\u001b[2m — \u001b[0m\u001b[1m\u001b[36mworkflow-agent\u001b[0m\u001b[2m · \u001b[0m\u001b[95mclaude-code/opus\u001b[0m\u001b[2m · \u001b[0m\u001b[2msession tutorial-16-workflow\u001b[0m \u001b[2m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m│\u001b[0m \u001b[2mType /help for commands. AI output may be inaccurate.\u001b[0m                            \u001b[2m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n\u001b[1m\u001b[96m\u001b[100m❯ Run a feature-planning workflow for adding a --verbose flag to this CLI. First surface the workflow-level\r\n  acceptance criteria. Then run two stages: an explore stage that maps where ar"]
[301.101923, "o", "gument parsing and output happen,\r\n  and a plan stage that drafts an ordered implementation approach — threading each stage into your workflow\r\n  dossier. Then FINALIZE as :partial. Do NOT run an exec stage and do NOT write any code into the project — this\r\n  is recommend-only. Take the finalize as a deliberate two-step (helper fence, then the answer with your\r\n  contract line).\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m[\u001b[0m\u001b[92m✓\u001b[0m\u001b[2m] \u001b[0m\u001b[1;97mIteration 1 / 100\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(8.5s)\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m[\u001b[0m\u001b[92m✓\u001b[0m\u001b[2m] \u001b[0m\u001b[1;97mIteration 2 / 100\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(52318 tok)\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(2m 12s)\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m  Think: \u001b[0m\u001b[2mTurn 1, no real history. The user wants a feature-planning workflow for adding a --verbose flag. I \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2mneed to: bootstrap the dossier first, surface acceptance criteria, then run explore + plan stages, \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2mthen FINALIZE as :partial (two-step). No exec, recommend-only. Step 1: Resolve template. Let me list \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2mtemplates and find a feature-planning / feature-launch fit. Compute determinist"]
[301.101941, "o", "ic id, probe resume, \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2mthen bootstrap. I'll do this in one clojure fence to gather template + id + resume state first, then \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2mbootstrap based on what's available. Let me start by discovering templates and computing the id.\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[2m• Code:\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m┌─\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m(def templates (:templates (workflow$list-templates)))\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m(println \"TEMPLATES:\")\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m(doseq [t templates] (println \"-\" (:id t) \"|\" (:source t) \"|\" (:description t)))\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m(def wid (:slug (workflow$id :template :feature-launch\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m                             :question \"Run a feature-planning workflow for adding a --verbose flag to\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35mthis CLI\")))\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m(println \"WID:\" wid)\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m(println \"RESUME:\" (workflow$resume? :id wid))\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m└─\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[2m• Output:\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m┌─\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0mTEMPLATES:\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0mWID: fea"]
[301.101993, "o", "ture-launch--feature-planning-workflow-adding-verbose-flag-cli\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0mRESUME: {:exists? false}\r\n    \u001b[2m└─\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m[\u001b[0m\u001b[92m✓\u001b[0m\u001b[2m] \u001b[0m\u001b[1;97mIteration 3 / 100\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(124840 tok)\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(47.1s)\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m  Think: \u001b[0m\u001b[2mIteration 2 showed templates list printed empty (no built-in feature-launch found via list-templates \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2mdoseq), but WID computed and resume says not-exists. I should try loading the feature-launch template \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2mdirectly (load-template resolves built-ins via classpath even if list didn't show them). If it loads, \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2mbootstrap with its acceptance + stages but tailor stages to the user's request: explore + plan only \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2m(no exec — recommend-only). If load fails, fall back to :ad-hoc with hand-drafted stages. Let me load \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2mthe template and inspect it first, then bootstrap. I'll do the load + inspect in one fence so I can \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2msee acceptance/stages structure before bootstrapping.\u001b"]
[301.102034, "o", "[0m\r\n  \u001b[2m• Code:\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m┌─\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m(def tmpl-load (workflow$load-template :id :feature-launch))\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m(println \"LOAD-SOURCE:\" (:source tmpl-load))\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m(println \"LOAD-ERROR:\" (:error tmpl-load))\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m(def tmpl (:template tmpl-load))\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m(println \"WF-ID:\" (:workflow/id tmpl))\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m(println \"WF-NAME:\" (:workflow/name tmpl))\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m(println \"ACCEPTANCE:\")\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m(doseq [a (:acceptance tmpl)] (println \"  -\" (:id a) \"|\" (:text a) \"| status:\" (:status a)))\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m(println \"STAGES:\")\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m(doseq [s (:stages tmpl)]\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m  (println \"  -\" (:id s) \"| agent:\" (or (:recommended-agent s) (:agent s))\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m           \"| gate-after:\" (:gate-after s) \"| focus:\" (:acceptance-focus s)))\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m(println \"DEFAULTS:\" (:defaults tmpl))\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m└─\u001b[0m\r\n "]
